  "text": "mGITR mRNA is mainly expressed in immature and mature T cells as shown in Table 1 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . mGITR expression in T cells was originally confirmed by flow-cytometric studies [CITATION_4] , and since then several studies have dealt with GITR expression in naïve or activated T cell sub-populations (Table 1) . Although some studies consider GITR expression peculiar to Treg cells (CD4 + CD25 + T cells having a regulatory function) [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] , mGITR and hGITR expression was found on the surface of both CD4 + and CD8",
